HEADWORD: Hyostylic
<hw>Hy`o*styl"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Hyo-</ets>
+ Gr. <?/ a pillar.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Having the mandible
suspended by the hyomandibular, or upper part of the hyoid arch, as in
fishes, instead of directly articulated with the skull as in mammals; --
said of the skull.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

